overview: The user initiated the project by providing a Statement of Work for a
  Sleep Questionnaire Application, seeking to integrate a database, an admin
  dashboard, and an authentication system. The primary goal was to store
  questionnaire responses, allow clients to access this data via a dashboard,
  and ensure secure access. The plan involved updating the application's
  demographics fields, creating a Prisma model for questionnaire responses in a
  PostgreSQL database (NeonDB), and developing API endpoints for data
  submission, retrieval, and CSV export. A key decision was to implement a
  simple password-based authentication system. Initially, a custom session
  management approach was taken, but this was later refined and simplified by
  leveraging Next.js middleware for more efficient route protection and session
  handling. An admin dashboard was built to display responses and facilitate CSV
  downloads. The questionnaire form was updated to ensure data was correctly
  submitted to the new database. During testing, it was discovered that the
  "Pre-fill & Jump to Report" button did not trigger a database save, leading to
  a direct API test to confirm database functionality. The final outcome is a
  fully integrated system with a functional database, a secure admin dashboard,
  and a streamlined authentication process.
